Obama Talks European Debt Crisis With Merkel, Sarkozy, Cameron

-- B y   R o g e r   R u n n i n g e n
-- 
2011-10-20T20:39:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/obama-talks-european-debt-crisis-with-merkel-sarkozy-cameron.html
     Oct. 20 (Bloomberg) --President Barack Obama held a
videoconference with German Chancellor  Angela Merkel , French
President  Nicolas Sarkozy  and British Prime Minister David Cameron to discuss Libya and the European financial crisis, the
White House said.  “Chancellor Merkel and President Sarkozy fully understand
the urgency of the issues in the Eurozone and are working
diligently to develop a comprehensive solution that addresses
the challenge and which will be politically sustainable,” the
statement said, without adding any details.  “They agreed to continue to consult closely” before the
Group of 20 nations summit in Cannes Nov. 3-4, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Roger Runningen in Washington at 
